    "This spectrum transitions from blue through green to yellow, serving as an indicator of the temporal sequence of the published works.",
    "The blue hues indicate foundational research, while the progression to yellow hues represents the more contemporary contributions in the field.",
    "Figure 3 sets out a graphical abstract of bibliometric networks that encapsulate a variety of terms pertinent to GeoGebra and its diverse utilities.",
    "Noteworthy lexical items include \"drawing\", \"diagram\", \"calculation\", \"its applications\", \"college mathematics\", \"mathematics teaching\", \"technology-based learning\", \"research\", \"open system\", \"mathematics\", \"objects\", \"technology accepted model\", \"mathematical software\" and \"open-source software\", each manifested on a chromatic scale from blue to green.",
    "This chromatic spectrum is indicative of their prevalence in scholarly publications in the years 2007-2015."
